From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Quenchforge Contributors <maintainers@cerid-ai.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 19:15:39 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] metal: gate support_simdgroup_reduction to Apple Silicon only
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Same root cause as llama.cpp#19563 in this older single-file
ggml-metal.m structure. The simdgroup-reduction kernels produce wrong
arithmetic on non-Apple Metal devices (Intel Mac + AMD discrete).
Gate to MTLGPUFamilyApple7 only by default; operators can opt back in
with GGML_METAL_FORCE_SIMDGROUP_REDUCTION=1.

bark.cpp's audio output regresses to noise without this fix on AMD
Vega II, even though the chain (bark.cpp → encodec.cpp → ggml) is
buried behind two submodule levels from the bark-server's perspective.

Upstream-Issue: https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp/issues/19563
EOF
)

Signed-off-by: Quenchforge Contributors <maintainers@cerid-ai.com>
---
 src/ggml-metal.m | 12 ++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/encodec.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-metal.m b/encodec.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-metal.m
index 172a0f9..2d5735e 100644
--- a/encodec.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-metal.m
+++ b/encodec.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-metal.m
@@ -55,8 +55,16 @@
     if (ctx->mtl_device == nil) {
         ctx->mtl_device = MTLCreateSystemDefaultDevice();
 
-        ctx->support_simdgroup_reduction  = [ctx->mtl_device supportsFamily:MTLGPUFamilyApple7];
-        ctx->support_simdgroup_reduction |= [ctx->mtl_device supportsFamily:MTLGPUFamilyMetal3_GGML];
+        // Quenchforge patch: simdgroup-reduction kernels rely on
+        // Apple-Silicon-specific simdgroup intrinsics. On non-Apple Metal
+        // devices (Intel Mac + AMD discrete, Intel iGPU) they produce wrong
+        // arithmetic. Same root cause as llama.cpp#19563. Older-style
+        // ggml-metal.m here uses `support_simdgroup_reduction` rather than
+        // `has_simdgroup_reduction` but the fix is identical.
+        ctx->support_simdgroup_reduction = [ctx->mtl_device supportsFamily:MTLGPUFamilyApple7];
+        if (getenv("GGML_METAL_FORCE_SIMDGROUP_REDUCTION") != NULL) {
+            ctx->support_simdgroup_reduction |= [ctx->mtl_device supportsFamily:MTLGPUFamilyMetal3_GGML];
+        }
 
         ctx->support_simdgroup_mm = [ctx->mtl_device supportsFamily:MTLGPUFamilyApple7];
 
-- 
